<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
An electronic article retrieved from an online source uses the same format as a printed journal 
article with the addition of the database name that it was retrieved from and, if available, a 
Digital Object Identifier (DOI). The 
<a href="http://www.crossref.org/guestquery" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
	DOI resolver
</a> 
can be used to find a DOI from the citation details if it is not given on the publication.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format for articles with a doi</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	Author, Initial(s) Year of publication, &#8216;Title of article&#8217;, <em>Title of Journal</em>, 
	volume number, issue number, page numbers, date viewed, database, DOI.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Jackson</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">D</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Firtko</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">A</span> &amp;
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Edenborough</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">M</span>
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2007</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">&#8216;Personal resilience as a strategy for surviving and thriving in the face of workplace adversity: a literature review&#8217;</span>,
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Journal">Journal of Advanced Nursing</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Volume">vol. 60</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Issue">no. 1</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Page numbers">pp. 1&#45;9</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Date Viewed">viewed 2 April 2009</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Database">Academic Search Complete database, EBSCOHost</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="DOI">DOI10.1111/j.1365&#45;2648.2007.04412.x</span>.
</blockquote>
